Nissan Motor Co Ltd &lt;NSAN.T> said it hasstarted to market a remodelled version of its four wheel drive(4WD) Safari vehicle in Japan.    Nissan said in a statement it hopes to sell 250 vehicles amonth in Japan.    It also plans soon to start exporting 3,400 vehicles amonth to the Australian, Middle East and Asian markets underthe name Patrol, a spokesman said.    It will sell the vehicle in Europe sometime in the future,with shipments from &lt;Motor Iberica S.A.>, its Spanish unit. Thevolume for Europe will be set later. REUTER&#3;